{{Infobox artwork | image_file = Cubi-xi.JPG | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 300px | title = Cubi XI | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[David Smith (sculptor)|David Smith]] | year = 1963 | type = sculpture | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = 92 | width_imperial = 29 | length_imperial = 38 | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = Washington, D.C. | museum = [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]] | coordinates = {{coord|38.891389|-77.023056}} | owner = National Gallery of Art }}
'''''Cubi XI''''' is an abstract sculpture by [[David Smith (sculptor)| David Smith]]. It is a part of the [[Cubi]] series of sculptures.
Constructed in 1963, it was installed on April 21, 1964 at 1875 [[Connecticut Avenue]], N.W. near [[Sheridan Circle]].<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/10/13/AR2006101300322.html| title=FROM THE COLLECTION: Washington's Prize Possessions| date=October 15, 2006 | author=Paul Richard| work=The Washington Post}}</ref><ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=127K28634C79V.34390&profile=ariall&uri=link=3100009~!1184006~!3100001~!3100002entories&term=Cubi+XI,&index=ALTIT#focus "Cubi XI (sculpture)"], ''SIRIS''</ref><ref>http://www.dcmemorials.com/index_indiv0001664.htm</ref><ref>http://www.satelliteviews.net/cgi-bin/g.cgi?fid=530660&state=DC&ftype=park</ref> It is in the [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]]. <ref>http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM9DHR_Cubi_XI_Washington_DC</ref>
