The Integrated Criminal Case Filing and Management System ('''ICMS Singapore''') is an internet-based system by the [[State Courts of Singapore]]. ICMS enables all criminal proceedings within the [[State Courts of Singapore]] to be conducted in an electronic environment using digital documents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lsc.gov.sg/OLY%202014_CJ%27s%20Speech.pdf|title=RESPONSE BY CHIEF JUSTICE SUNDARESH MENON OPENING OF THE LEGAL YEAR 2014}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.justpal.org/documents/10179/34346/SINGAPORE%20-%20Mr.%20James%20Leong%20%28Surbodinate%20Courts%29%20Electronic%20Court%20Case%20Management%20Systems.pdf|title=The World Bank’s JUSTPAL eJustice Conference: The Supreme Court of Georgia and The World Bank Tbilisi, Georgia, 10 – 11 January 2012, Electronic Court Case Management: The Singapore Subordinate Courts Experience by James Leong, District Judge and Senior Director, Strategic Planning and Training Division, Subordinate Courts of Singapore}}</ref>
==ICMS for Government Agencies== All Singapore government agencies involved in criminal justice system are linked to the ICMS.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlaw.gov.sg/news/speeches/speech-by-min-at-criminal-law-conference-2014.html|title=Speech by Minister for Foreign Affairs and Law, K Shanmugam, at the Criminal Law Conference 2014|accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> The agencies can do the following process with the [[State Courts of Singapore]] directly from their office without a courthouse visit. These process include, criminal prosecutions, file applications and receive court orders.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statecourts.gov.sg/Resources/Documents/AnnualReport2013.pdf|title=ANNUAL REPORT 2013|accessdate=2015-06-01}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/news/singapore/courts-crime/story/state-courts-implement-new-computer-system-save-time-and-resources|title=State Courts implement new computer system to save time and resources|author=Amir Hussain|work=Straitstimes.com|accessdate=2015-06-04}}</ref>
